author: Diane Daniel
title: Seneca Art and Culture Center to Open in October - The New York Times
text:
Continue reading the main story Share This Page Continue reading the main story Continue reading the main story Seneca Center The Seneca Art and Culture Center opens Oct. 3 at Ganondagan State Historic Site in Victor, N.Y., 20 miles southeast of Rochester . The center is built on the site of the original Seneca settlement, destroyed in 1687. The gallery will offer changing exhibitions conveying the story of the Seneca and Haudenosaunee (also known as Iroquois) people through centuries of artistic and historical artifacts and will also include work from contemporary Native American artists.
